  "title": "component-hook-factories",
  "content": "Validates against higher order functions defining nested components or hooks. Components and hooks should be defined at the module level.\n\nDefining components or hooks inside other functions creates new instances on every call. React treats each as a completely different component, destroying and recreating the entire component tree, losing all state, and causing performance problems.\n\nExamples of incorrect code for this rule:\n\nExamples of correct code for this rule:\n\nYou might think you need a factory to create customized components:\n\nPass JSX as children instead:",
